  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty in boundary conditions and blood rheology parameters was quantified via Monte Carlo propagation across 500 replicate simulations; a screening sensitivity study was conducted internally to identify which inputs contributed most to hemolysis index variance, but results are summarized only in the UQ narrative and have not been linked as a structured sensitivity analysis record.",
