      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified with reference to rotating machinery benchmark data; hemolysis power-law model validated against published erythrocyte damage data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published rotating machinery validation studies showing superior performance near wall regions. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model parameters validated against erythrocyte lysis data from literature (R²=0.91). Model form uncertainty estimated at ±15% NIH and incorporated into UQ analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key input parameters (viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profile) characterized with probability distributions derived from literature and experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across 500 replicate simulations sampling blood viscosity (log-normal, CV=8%), density (normal, CV=0.3%), hemolysis model coefficient C (uniform ±20%), and inlet turbulence intensity (uniform 3–8%). Combined 95% prediction interval for NIH is ±19% at worst-case operating point. A screening sensitivity study was conducted to identify dominant contributors to NIH variance; viscosity and model coefficient C were found most influential. Input uncertainty is adequately characterized for MRL 2 purposes."
    },
