    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 given medium model influence. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo analysis demonstrates that NIH predictions satisfy RH < 1 criterion with 95% confidence across all five CPB operating points. The assessment team reviewed the UQ narrative, which references an internal screening sensitivity study identifying blood viscosity and hemolysis model coefficient C as dominant variance contributors. The overall evidence package supports acceptance of the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions in support of the Class II CPB device submission.",
